Package: BayRC
Type: Package
Title: Bayesian Framework for Comparative Circadian Genomics
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Thien", "Pham", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "quythien14@gmail.com"),
    person("Kyle", "Kauffman", role = "aut"))
Description: BayRC (Bayesian Rhythmicity Comparison) provides a unified
    Bayesian framework for detecting conserved and altered circadian rhythms
    across conditions, tissues, or species. It implements Reversible Jump MCMC
    for gene-level Bayesian cosinor modelling, Bayesian FDR control for rhythm
    transition classification (gain/loss/conservation), circular phase
    concordance analysis, pathway-level enrichment, and genome-wide concordance
    scoring with permutation-based inference.
